@mzfr it is a common practice to mark addons as broken when they stop working or are no longer maintained. This is achieved by setting the <broken></broken> element in addon.xml with a message explaining the reasoning (of the addon being broken). Consider the use case in which an addon exists in a lower Repo (Gotham) and was marked as broken due to  being no longer maintained. If someone decides to take the ownership of the said addon, to fix it and submit it to krypton there is no reason for the CI to flag any "issue". 

Recently i marked one of my addons (screensaver.atv4) as broken in the helix Repo and moved it to krypton as it is a skinned addon and required methods introduced in the skinning API with krypton. Being " warned" with each update I send from now on due to an outdated and explicitly tagged broken addon present in helix does not make much sense.
Hope the explanation was clear enough.

I just found a simple fix to this issue: 

```python
def escape_item(self, item):
    if isinstance(item, (int, float)):
        return self.escape_number(item)
    elif isinstance(item, basestring):
        return self.escape_string(item)
    elif item is None:
        return 'NULL'
    else:
        raise exc.ProgrammingError("Unsupported object {}".format(item))
        
import pyhive
pyhive.common.ParamEscaper.escape_item = escape_item
```

Please let me know if this would be an acceptable fix and I can contribute a pull request.  

Thanks,
Pedro

